<subSubSection id="4A84A9C7872F6D4F37B72983FB8E0040" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0221FA4C872F6D4F37B72983FF6C01C8" blockId="3.[144,1104,653,813]" box="[144,252,653,676]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">
<heading id="59694D20872F6D4F37B72983FF6C01C8" box="[144,252,653,676]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480" reason="5">
<emphasis id="30EA265E872F6D4F37B72983FF6C01C8" box="[144,252,653,676]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0221FA4C872F6D4F37B729BAFB8E0040" blockId="3.[144,1104,653,813]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">
Leptoplanoidea with varying outline of the body. Ruffled pharynx arranged centrally or somewhat anterior. Male copulatory apparatus directed backwards, behind pharynx. True prostatic vesicle of 
<taxonomicName id="C59E81CF872F6D4F36C429FAFDC70060" box="[483,599,756,780]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Notoplana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="30EA265E872F6D4F36C429FAFDC70060" box="[483,599,756,780]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">Notoplana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="DD2544EE872F6D4F354729FBFD000061" box="[608,656,757,781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">type</typeStatus>
present; its glandular lining epithelium is subdivided into a great number of elongate tubular chambers (atomata 
<typeStatus id="DD2544EE872F6D4F34FA281AFB810040" box="[989,1041,788,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">type</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
